Long ago, in a land far, far away,
there was a boy whose smiling face
was more radiant than any jewel.
His affirming upbringing only served
to enhance his natural charisma.

That boy's name was Chitose,
and he embraced his lot in life.
So bubbly was his disposition
that he shined bright like the sun.

Yet as surely as a storm spoils a
picnic, there came a day when the
thunderclap of expectation
threatened his sunny nature.
Your coming-of-age ceremony will be upon\nus before long, Chitose. Accordingly,\nyou will be taking your examination.
Father, no. I don't want to.
Refusal is not an option. You cannot\npersist in interminable fascination with\n＂cuteness＂!
You must become a strong, stout man—\none befitting our role as a warrior family\nin service of the Mouse Clan.
You keep saying that, but I haven't the\nfaintest idea how to do what you ask.
I suspected you would say as much.\nThat is why I made arrangements for\nyou to call upon the Boar Clan.
Master Ieyasu will model for you\nthe strength and mindset I expect\nyou to embody. Now, off you go!
And so, I need to learn what it\nmeans to be a ＂strong, stout man.＂
Ha ha. I admit I found myself curious as to\nwhy the Mouse Clan had petitioned me for\naid, and here we have it.
I am sorry to trouble you with this,\nMaster Ieyasu.

It's no bother at all; the coming-of-age
ceremony is a major life event for one born
to a warrior family of Hinomoto. It weighs
on your father just as it weighs on you.
Now, as for what constitutes a strong,\nstout man... Addis, to me, please.
Whoa, he looks so cool and strong!
Indeed. And if I had to hazard a guess,\nI'd say that your father hopes for you to\nbecome like Addis here.
Addis sports a sturdy physique and\nis as martially adept as they come.
I wonder if this is the kind of man your\nfather is imagining when he uses the\nwords ＂strong＂ and ＂stout.＂
What?! W-wait, are you saying that...
...in order to become a strong man,\nI have to stop being cute?!
I mean, I ain't never thought of myself\nas cute.
I KNEW IT! But wait. Waaait a sec. WAIT.
If you take the cute outta me, I'll basically\njust be a lifeless husk! You can't do that!\nNO WAY, NO HOW!
Calm your heart. If you are truly so vexed\nby the idea, then perhaps a conversation\nwith your father is in order.
You mustn't coddle him, Master Ieyasu.
So long as a person lives, they cannot\nstop growing—in neither mind nor body.
In neither mind NOR body? So you're\nsaying I'm going to end up all muscled\nout like Addis?!
I don't want that, though! I want to stay\nlike I am now—cute in mind and body!\nHow can I do that?!
You cannot. You can but accept that\nchange is inevitable.
(People have been telling me how cute I\nam all my life. It's made me so happy.)
(But now I'm suddenly supposed to just\nbe at peace with changing who I am? No!)
I hate the thought of becoming an adult.\nEven Lady Mitsuhide has been totally\ndifferent since she made her soulpact.
I know that she's still the same person,\nbut it makes me sad that things have\nto change.
I don't want to be an adult. I just want\nto freeze time and live like this forever.
What do I have to do to stay cute forever?
Pull yourself together, Chitose! What's\ngoing on in that head of yours? You\nhaven't slept a wink, and you're not eating!
I don't know where this stubborn streak\ncame from all of a sudden. You need to\ngrow up and—
Omigosh, ENOUGH! Shut up about the\nadult stuff already! I don't want to\n＂grow up＂!
I'm staying cute—in mind AND in body—\nand that's that! I don't ever want to change!\nI'm going to...stop things...as they...
Someone, help! Please! I need medical\nassistance, or else...or else my boy is\ngoing to die!
